name: 2-Methoxyethanol
Reason: 2-Methoxyethanol is a derivative of ethanol, which has a melting point of -114.1°C. The presence of a methoxy group (-OCH3) in 2-Methoxyethanol increases the melting point due to the hydrogen bonding capability of the ether oxygen atom. The melting point increase can be estimated to be around 10-20°C.
